- CloudHSM(Hardware Security Module)=> AWS provisions encryption Hardware
- You amange your encryption keys entirely
- Tamper resistant, FIPS 140-2 Level 3 compliance
- Both symmetric and assymetric key(SSL/TLS)encryption
- Good option to use with SSE-C encryption
- Redshift supports CloudHSM for database encryption and key management
- There is a cloudHSM client
- AWS only provides you CRUD for cloudHSM cluster
- Using cloudHSM software you can manage users and keys